==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Odor
<hw>O"dor</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"d⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>odor</ets>, <ets>odour</ets>, OF. <ets>odor</ets>,
<ets>odour</ets>, F. <ets>odeur</ets>, fr. L. <ets>odor</ets>; akin to
<ets>olere</ets> to smell, Gr. <grk>'o`zein</grk>, Lith.
<ets>⟦uring⟧sti</ets>. Cf. <er>Olfactory</er>, <er>Osmium</er>,
<er>Ozone</er>, <er>Redolent</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>odour</asp>.]</altsp> <def>Any smell, whether fragrant or
offensive; scent; perfume.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Meseemed I smelt a garden of sweet flowers,⟦br⟧
That dainty <qex>odors</qex> from them threw around.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To be in bad odor</b></col>, <cd>to be out of favor, or
in bad repute.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Odorament</ent>⟦br⟧
